1 Introduction
**************

‘org-comments’ adds review comments to Org buffers while keeping the
source Org text clean.  Local comments are stored in colocated
‘.comments.org’ sidecar files.  Remote systems such as Confluence can
register backends for comment synchronization, remote opening, push, and
pull operations.

   The package is intentionally backend-neutral.  Its core model
describes comment identity, target text, replies, local draft state,
remote state, sync state, people identity, and actionability without
requiring a specific provider.  Confluence is one backend; Google Docs
or another review system can implement the same protocol later.

   This manual is written as an Emacs Info manual.  After building it,
browse it with ‘C-h i m org-comments RET’.


