2.1 Requirements
================

   • Emacs with Org mode available.
   • A writable directory next to each commented Org source file for
     local sidecar files.
   • Optional backend packages for remote providers, such as
     ‘org-confluence’.


File: org-comments.info,  Node: Installation from a checkout,  Next: Minimal workflow,  Prev: Requirements,  Up: Getting Started

2.2 Installation from a checkout
================================

Add the package directory to ‘load-path’ and require the package:

     (add-to-list 'load-path "/path/to/org-comments")
     (require 'org-comments)

   Then enable ‘org-comments-mode’ in Org buffers.  This minor mode is
the main user entry point for commands, keybindings, and overlays:

     (add-hook 'org-mode-hook #'org-comments-mode)

   For a commands-only setup without inline/page markers, set
‘org-comments-enable-overlays’ before enabling the mode:

     (setq org-comments-enable-overlays nil)
     (add-hook 'org-mode-hook #'org-comments-mode)


File: org-comments.info,  Node: Minimal workflow,  Prev: Installation from a checkout,  Up: Getting Started

2.3 Minimal workflow
====================

  1. Open an Org file.
  2. Enable ‘org-comments-mode’.
  3. Select a region and run ‘M-x org-comments-create’.
  4. Open the side panel with ‘M-x org-comments-open’.
  5. Navigate comments with ‘org-comments-next’ and
     ‘org-comments-previous’.

   See *note Commands:: and *note Keybindings:: for the generated
reference.


