6.1 Identity resolution
=======================

Backends can set ‘org-comments-resolve-account-id-function’ to resolve
remote account IDs into display names for sidecar headings and UI
surfaces.  The callback is called with an account ID and optional
directory context, and should return a display name string or nil.  This
keeps provider-specific people stores outside the generic ‘org-comments’
package.


File: org-comments.info,  Node: Confluence Backend,  Next: Migration,  Prev: Backends,  Up: Top

7 Confluence Backend
********************

The Confluence integration lives in ‘org-confluence’.  When a source Org
buffer contains ‘#+CONFLUENCE_PAGE_ID’, the Confluence detector can
select the ‘confluence’ backend for remote comment operations.

   The backend supports remote open, push, pull, and comments-only sync.
Full Confluence page synchronization remains an ‘org-confluence’
responsibility and is intentionally separate from ‘org-comments-sync’.


File: org-comments.info,  Node: Migration,  Next: Commands,  Prev: Confluence Backend,  Up: Top

8 Migration
***********

Older sidecars may contain ‘HUB_COMMENT_*’ properties.  Run
‘org-comments-migrate-sidecar’ on one sidecar, or
‘org-comments-migrate-directory-sidecars’ for a directory of sidecars,
to rewrite those properties to ‘ORG_COMMENTS_*’.

   Migration is explicit by design.  Durable storage should not depend
on the former personal metadata prefix.


